        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 2:23PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 223 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Dayton, or near Virginia City, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carson City, Virginia City, Dayton, Washoe City, Damonte Ranch,
Pleasant Valley, Carson City Airport, Galena, New Washoe City, Indian
Hills, Washoe Lake Campground, Us 395 At Douglas-Carson City Co Line,
Lakeview, Rawe Peak, Gold Hill, Davis Creek Campground, Stewart,
Junction U.S 50 And Six Mile Canyon-Ft Churchill Rd, Us 50 At Carson
City-Lyon Co Line, and Junction U.S 50 And NV 341.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
